Meet <b>Angi</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Angi lives at <a href='/home/?user=motis'>1685 Bluff Creek Circle</a> in the lovely, picturesque area of Lakeview.  A citizen of Millsberry since August 15th of 2004, she has already made quite an impression on the community!<br><br>Thanks to her charismatic nature, Angi has many friends who love hanging out with her, and she loves to hang out with them, too.  Sometimes, after school, she likes to head over to her best friend's house.  Angi keeps all her friends constantly laughing with her great sense of humor, and whenever they can't find something to do, she entertains them with her growing collection of magic tricks.<br><br>As far as school, Angi is a model student at Millsberry Academy.  Her teachers describe her as a very knowledgeable young lady, whose sharp mind has earned her many awards, including a gold trophy for mastering Solver.  When Angi isn't learning things for school, she is usually studying up on animals.  She is very interested in all sorts of different animals, and on weekends, you can sometimes find Angi with her friends at a zoo, enthusiastically observing all the creatures.<br><br>When she doesn't feel like traveling, however, Angi often retreats to her tree house, a small but cozy construction that is decorated in her favorite colors of green, tan, and pink.  Inside this little space, Angi usually spends her time writing and listening to the soothing sounds of classical music and soft rock. However, when the mood strikes her, she'll occasionally put on a few catchy show tune numbers.<br><br>Angi's friends aren't the only ones who appreciate her.  All of Millsberry has plenty of reasons to be thankful she lives here, due to the tremendous effort she's made to help keep Peabody Park clean.  Angi also recently made a sizable donation to the Community Center Building Fund, which will certainly be put to good use.<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Angi, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
